snippet.textDisplay: Imagine being in that room! I know people have opinions (On the internet???) Personally; The similarities from 2 men who couldn't be more "oppisite" has quite a bit of irony in it. Mike was a BEAST in the ring! To see the transformation of his entire mindset, lifestyle, behavior, perception on & on. Not only is that almost unheard of, To me it's more impressive than he was in the ring. (& I don't feel anyone to date could compare on all the technical aspects he excelled at) Em current day & THIS interview, I feel safe to say, is the most open & candid we have ever seen him. 2 Men that I wouldn't want to face in either of their areas of expertise, As they are both master's of their craft. I have slacked following boxing, I'm an avid hip hop head. ALL of that aside; The struggles & challenges they have both endured & overcome, The honesty & humility, Respect for one another, Most impressive, I felt, was just how down to earth & in touch with reality 2 Guy's who DON'T have to do this! Don't NEED to do this! A lot of lessons to be learned in this one! I salute & Respect you both + Appreciate you both doing this! T.Y.!
